Class VectorEntryActions

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.thomsonreuters.upa.codec.VectorEntryActions

  • public class VectorEntryActions
extends java.lang.Object
    VectoryEntryAction helps to manage change processing rules and informs the consumer of how to apply the entry's data.

    • Field Detail

      • UPDATE

        public static final int UPDATE
        Indicates that the consumer should update any previously stored or displayed information with the contents of this entry. An update action typically occurs when an entry is already set or inserted and changes to the contents are required. If an update action occurs prior to the set or insert action for the same entry, the update action should be ignored. UPDATE can apply to both sortable and non-sortable vectors.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SET

        public static final int SET
        Indicates that the consumer should set the entry at this index position. A set action typically occurs when an entry is initially provided. It is possible for multiple set actions to target the same entry. If this occurs, any previously received data associated with the entry should be replaced with the newly-added information. SET can apply to both sortable and non-sortable vectors.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • CLEAR

        public static final int CLEAR
        Indicates that the consumer should remove any stored or displayed information associated with this entry's index position. CLEAR can apply to both sortable and non-sortable vectors. No entry payload is included when the action is a 'clear.'
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • INSERT

        public static final int INSERT
        Applies only to a sortable vector. The consumer should insert this entry at the index position. Any higher order index positions are incremented by one (e.g., if inserting at index position 5 the existing position 5 becomes 6, existing position 6 becomes 7, and so on).
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • DELETE

        public static final int DELETE
        Applies only to a sortable vector. The consumer should remove any stored or displayed data associated with this entry's index position. Any higher order index positions are decremented by one (e.g., if deleting at index position 5 the existing position 5 is removed, position 6 becomes 5, position 7 becomes 6, and so on). No entry payload is included when the action is a 'delete.'
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
